:"The cousin marriage was paralleled in the family: William Henry's brother Thomas Harvey Hooker had also married a Shader-line Hooker cousin (Caroline E. Shader, Lydia's aunt). Two brothers Thomas Edwin Hooker's sons each thus married a Shader-line Hooker woman, making their offspring doubly Hooker-descended on both maternal and paternal sides. The pattern thickened the Hooker-line concentration in the Murray, Orleans County New York branch."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Born Murray NY 1864, three children with Lydia","body":"William Henry Hooker was born August 18, 1864 in Murray, Orleans County New York — the eldest child of Thomas Edwin Hooker by his second wife Susan M. Brown. He died May 15, 1933 in Brockport, Monroe County New York at age sixty-eight, buried at Beach Ridge Cemetery Brockport. He had three children with Lydia: C. Theodore Hooker (1891-1971), Ethel Susan Hooker Zastrow (1896-1928 died young at 31), and Marjory Violetta Hooker Delahanty (1902-1993)."}],"cross_connections":[],"burial":{"plot_notes":"Beach Ridge Cemetery, Brockport, Monroe County NY (per Findagrave). Same as wife Lydia Mason Robinson Hooker."},"nickname":"Willie","residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"william-hooker-1864"},"neighborhood":{"focus":{"id":"H03880","slug":"william-hooker-1864","n":"William Henry Hooker","by":1864,"dy":1933,"sx":"m","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":9},"spouses":[{"order":1,"spouse":{"id":"HD3270","slug":"lydia-hooker-1865","n":"Lydia Mason Robinson Hooker","by":1865,"dy":1915,"sx":"u","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":10},"year":1890,"children":[{"id":"HD3236","slug":"c-hooker-1891","n":"C Theodore Hooker","by":1891,"dy":1971,"sx":"m","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":10},{"id":"HD3237","slug":"ethel-zastrow-1896","n":"Ethel Susan Hooker Zastrow","by":1896,"dy":1928,"sx":"f","