York — the eldest child of Thomas Edwin Hooker by his second wife Susan M. Brown. He died May 15, 1933 in Brockport, Monroe County New York at age sixty-eight, buried at Beach Ridge Cemetery Brockport. He had three children with Lydia: C. Theodore Hooker (1891-1971), Ethel Susan Hooker Zastrow (1896-1928 died young at 31), and Marjory Violetta Hooker Delahanty (1902-1993)."}],"cross_connections":[],"burial":{"plot_notes":"Beach Ridge Cemetery, Brockport, Monroe County NY (per Findagrave). Same as wife Lydia Mason Robinson Hooker."},"nickname":"Willie","residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"william-hooker-1864"},"HD3270":{"id":"HD3270","former_ids":["X02243"],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":true,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"is_easter_egg":false,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":10,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true},"bio":{"first_name":"Lydia","middle_name":"Mason","last_name":"Hooker","maiden_name":"Robinson","married_names":["Hooker"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Lydia Mason Robinson Hooker"},"birth":{"year":1865,"month":7,"day":9,"state":"New York","country":"United States","city":"Murray","county":"Orleans County"},"death":{"year":1915,"month":2,"day":8,"city":"Holley","county":"Orleans County","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"parents":{"father_id":"X02287","mother_id":"HD3269"},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"H03880","date_year":1889,"date_month":1,"date_day":19,"location_state":"New York","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death","end_year":1915,"children_ids":["HD3236","HD3237","HD3238"]}],"tags":["cousin_marriage"],"sources":[{"short":"EH 3880 (as William Henry Hooker spouse)"},{"short":"WikiTree + Findagrave"}],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Cousin marriage united two Hooker-line branches","body":"Lydia Mason Robinson married William Henry Hooker on January 19, 1889 — the marriage joining two Hooker-line branches in a single household. Lydia descended from Captain Thomas Hooker through her grandmother Laura Electa Hooker Shader (Myron Hooker's daughter); William Henry descended through the parallel Thomas Edwin Hooker branch. They were third cousins once removed, and their three children inherited double Hooker ancestry."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Three children, daughter Ethel died age thirty-one","body":"Lydia and William Henry had three children: Charles Theodore Hooker (1891-1971), Ethel Susan Hooker Zastrow (1896-1928 died young at thirty-one), and Marjory Violetta Hooker Delahanty (1902-1993). The Hooker-Zastrow line traces forward through Ethel; the Hebner-Cook-Stafford family that descended from these children is doubly Hooker-descended on both maternal and paternal sides."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Born Murray NY 1865, died Holley 1915","body":"Lydia Mason Robinson was born July 9 or 10, 1865 in Murray, Orleans County New York. She died February 8, 1915 in Holley, Orleans County New York at age forty-nine — predeceasing her husband William Henry by eighteen years. The Orleans County NY core of the Hooker-Shader-Robinson cousin network spanned three generations of intermarriages within the same upstate New York county."}],"cross_connections":[],"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"lydia-hooker-1865"},"HD3236":{"id":"HD3236","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"gender":"male","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_desce